          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-top:4px;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá∑üá∫ Russia - Putin visits Kursk.</strong> President Putin visited Russia‚Äôs Kursk region after expelling Ukrainian forces. Ukraine continues drone strikes, hitting a missile-linked plant in Oryol. Russia launched retaliatory missile attacks and intercepted 159 Ukrainian drones. A ceasefire remains elusive despite international pressure and recent talks between Putin and Trump (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-may-25-worldwide-6-putin-s-visit" target="_blank">Putin‚Äôs visit</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üáªüá¶ Vatican City - Pope Leo appeals for aid.</strong>  Pope Leo XIV urged Israel to allow more humanitarian aid into Gaza, calling the crisis "worrying and painful." He appealed for an end to hostilities, highlighting suffering among children and the elderly. Israel recently eased an 11-week aid blockade amid starvation warnings, but aid groups say it's insufficient (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-may-25-worldwide-7-pope-calls" target="_blank">Pope calls</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üáªüá™ Venezuela- Suspends flights to Colombia.</strong> Venezuela suspended flights from Colombia until May 26 after arresting 38 people accused of plotting pre-election attacks. Authorities allege links to foreign mercenaries and the opposition. The move follows reports of political repression after President Nicol√°s Maduro‚Äôs disputed 2024 re-election. Colombia denied knowledge of detained citizens (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-may-25-worldwide-8-colombia-disputes" target="_blank">Colombia disputes</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üáµüá∏ Palestine - Hamas official offends.</strong> A senior Hamas official, Sami Abu Zuhri, sparked outrage after calling Gaza‚Äôs massive war death toll ‚Äúmaterial calculations,‚Äù saying future births would replace the dead. His comments, made from exile in Qatar, went viral and drew furious backlash from Gaza residents, including street protests and social media condemnation (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-may-25-worldwide-9-tone-deaf-comments" target="_blank">tone deaf comments</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá´üá∑ France - Muslim Brotherhood.</strong> 
            A confidential French government report warns that the Muslim Brotherhood poses a long-term threat to national cohesion by spreading political Islamism at the local level. The report urges firm measures, citing risks to secularism and gender equality. Macron has called for policy proposals, stressing the importance of outreach to France‚Äôs Muslim community (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-may-25-worldwide-10-more-about-the-report" target="_blank">more about the report</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üáøüá¶ South Africa - Diplomatic tensions.</strong> 
            During a meeting between Donald Trump and South African President Cyril Ramaphosa, Trump repeated accusations of a white genocide in South Africa. Ramaphosa firmly rejects this while emphasizing South Africa's democratic values. He sarcastically apologized to Trump for not getting him a jet plane. The US recently admitted white South Africans as refugees, sparking criticism (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-05-2025-the-tea" target="_blank">the tea</a>).
